+### Per-fire sequence
+
+Each fire of the `reckoner.tick` relay runs a fixed sequence:
+
+1. **Resolve the active scheduler.** Throws fail-loud when pre-seal
+   (`phase:started` has not yet fired). Production never trips this
+   guard; misconfigured test fixtures get a deterministic loud
+   signal.
+2. **Re-read `reckoner.schedulerConfig`** and call the scheduler's
+   `validateConfig` narrower (when present). On throw: fail-loud log
+   via the `[reckoner] scheduler:` prefix and skip the entire tick
+   (no rows).
+3. **Query held petitions.** Read `clerk/writs` directly with
+   `phase = 'new'` (bypasses Clerk's `list()` because that path
+   applies an implicit `type = 'mandate'` filter when phase is
+   supplied without type). Filter to writs carrying `ext.reckoner`
+   with a non-empty source string.
+4. **Apply source/disabled gates inline.** Writs failing either
+   gate are declined and transitioned to cancelled, with one row
+   each. Disabled-source rows carry
+   `declineReason: 'source_banned'`; unregistered-source rows
+   under `enforceRegistration: true` carry
+   `declineReason: 'source_unregistered'`. Both decline shapes use
+   the same resolution-string template, differing only in the
+   final clause.
+5. **Filter the candidate set against the dedupe lookup.** Rows
+   already exist for `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` ⇒ skip — the
+   scheduler never sees them. Pre-write dedupe would have the
+   scheduler emit decisions the row-write layer silently discards,
+   hiding drift.
+6. **Build one `SchedulerInput { candidates, capacity, now, config }`**
+   with the v0 capacity stub and call `evaluate`. On throw or
+   non-array return: fail-loud log and skip the entire tick.
+7. **Validate decisions.** Filter-and-warn on stranger writIds
+   (apply only in-scope decisions). Fail-loud-skip the **entire
+   tick** on multi-decision-per-writ — no rows for any writ in that
+   tick.
+8. **Apply each decision** in candidate order: approve →
+   transition + accepted row; decline → transition + declined row;
+   defer → no transition + deferred row. `tickEventId` is stamped
+   from the triggering `clockworks.timer` event id when present and
+   omitted when absent (the `reckoner.tick` relay receives the
+   firing event id from Clockworks; test paths driving the handler
+   directly with `null` produce rows without the field).
 
 ### Failure modes
 
 | Condition                                                          | Behavior |
 |---|---|
-| CDC event arrives before `phase:started`                           | Silently skipped; the catch-up scan reprocesses the writ post-seal. |
-| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | No `evaluate` call, no acceptance/decline row, no transition. The dedupe runs inside the scheduler call and counts only non-deferred prior rows — the dependency gate (which runs *before* the scheduler) re-evaluates every tick regardless. |
-| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] scheduler:` prefix; evaluation is skipped (no row, no transition). |
-| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; evaluation skipped. |
-| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue. |
-| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the entire evaluation is skipped (no decision is applied). |
-| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; the decision is ignored. |
+| Tick fires before `phase:started`                                  | Throws fail-loud (`[reckoner] tick: activeScheduler not resolved …`). Production never trips it; test fixtures see a deterministic, loud error. |
+| Dedupe lookup short-circuits on the same `(writId, writUpdatedAt)` | Writ never reaches the scheduler; no `evaluate` call, no row, no transition. Counts only non-deferred prior rows — a defer keeps the writ available for re-evaluation on the next tick. |
+| `validateConfig` throws                                            | Fail-loud log via the `[reckoner] scheduler:` prefix; the entire tick is skipped (no rows). |
+| `evaluate` throws or does not return an array                      | Fail-loud log; the entire tick is skipped (no rows for any writ). |
+| Decision carries a `writId` not in the candidate set               | Per-decision `console.warn` naming the offending id; ignore-and-continue (in-scope decisions still apply). |
+| Two decisions target the same `writId`                             | Fail-loud log; the **entire tick** is skipped (no rows for any writ). |
+| Decision carries an unknown outcome                                | Fail-loud log; the offending decision is ignored. |
 
